            <title>[HIVE-5607] Hive fails to parse the &quot;%&quot; (mod) sign after brackets.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-5607</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;the scenario :&lt;br/&gt;
create table t(a int);&lt;br/&gt;
select * from t order by (a)%7;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;will fail with the following exception :&lt;br/&gt;
FAILED: ParseException line 1:28 mismatched input &apos;%&apos; expecting EOF near &apos;)&apos;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I must mention that this &lt;b&gt;does&lt;/b&gt; work in 0.7.1 and doesn&apos;t work in 0.10&lt;/p&gt;</description>
